modules.description: This module defines parsers for converting ANSI escape sequences into concrete text and item representations. It operates on lists of `Ansiparse.Concrete.t` values, using the Angstrom parsing library to process input streams. Concrete use cases include parsing raw terminal output into structured HTML elements by first transforming it into an intermediate list of styled text items.

Converts raw text with ANSI escape sequences into a structured list of styled text items, resets, and escape codes. Works with custom types representing text segments, styles like bold or underline, and color attributes. Used to transform terminal output into intermediate representations for rendering ANSI codes as HTML.

Translates lists of concrete ANSI items into nested abstract syntax trees representing styled text. Uses a tree structure with styled nodes and string leaves, tracking formatting state across nested levels. Useful for rendering ANSI-colored logs or terminal output into hierarchical HTML representations with proper style inheritance.

Converts ANSI-styled abstract syntax trees into HTML `<pre>` elements. Works with `Ansiparse.Abstract.t` values, which represent structured ANSI output, and produces valid HTML elements suitable for rendering in web contexts. Useful for displaying terminal output with color and formatting preserved in web interfaces.

Transforms ANSI escape sequences into structured text representations with styling information. Processes strings containing terminal control codes into typed data structures representing styled text segments, color changes, and formatting operations. Used to convert colored command-line output into HTML while preserving visual formatting.
